Durban - DNA results have confirmed that kidnapped Barrio businessman Sikhumbuzo Mjwara is dead. Mjwara was kidnapped outside the Verulam Magistrate's Court on August 30. DNA this week revealed that the bone fragments which was found in a cemetery in Pietermaritzburg in October belonged to Mjwara. According to a source close to the investigation the family were notified earlier this week. Four people - three policemen and a security guard - were arrested and charged. Pietermaritzburg security guard Nkosiphile Ndlovu who is believed to be the hitmen abandoned his bail application and remains in police custody. Ndlovu apparently did a pointing out to police of where Mjwara's remains were. The three policemen -Sergeant Thabane Cyril Ndlovu, Constable Collen Makhaye and Jerome Dumisani Ngubane were released on R3000 bail. All four face charges of murder and kidnapping. The motive is unknown. The Sunday Tribune reported that Mjwara, a former eThekwini Municipality employee, is the director of a chain of businesses, including several mining, investment and lifestyle companies. Daily News 